Document: JSON
Path: godot/classes/class_json.rst
Summary: Provides methods for converting Godot data types to and from JSON strings.
Inherits: Object

The JSON class enables all data types to be converted to and from a JSON string, useful for serializing data for saving or network transmission.

Method: stringify(value: Variant) → String
Converts any data type into a JSON string.

Method: parse(json_string: String) → int
Converts an existing JSON string into a Variant. Returns OK on success, or an error code on failure. Use get_error_message() and get_error_line() to retrieve details about the error.

Property: data (Variant)
The parsed Variant data. Available after a successful parse() call.

Method: parse_string(json_string: String) → Variant
A static method to parse JSON strings. Returns the parsed Variant or null if parsing fails. This method does not handle errors.

Note: Both parse methods have some deviations from the strict JSON specification:
- Trailing commas in arrays or objects are ignored.
- Newline and tab characters within string literals are accepted and treated as escape sequences (\n, \t).
- Numbers are parsed using String.to_float(), which is more lenient than the JSON standard.
- Some errors, like invalid Unicode sequences, do not cause a parser error but result in string cleanup and a console log.

GDScript:
    var data_to_send = ["a", "b", "c"]
    var json_string = JSON.stringify(data_to_send)
    # Save data
    # ...
    # Retrieve data
    var json = JSON.new()
    var error = json.parse(json_string)
    if error == OK:
        var data_received = json.data
        if typeof(data_received) == TYPE_ARRAY:
            print(data_received) # Prints the array.
        else:
            print("Unexpected data")
    else:
        print("JSON Parse Error: ", json.get_error_message(), " in ", json_string, " at line ", json.get_error_line())

GDScript:
    var data = JSON.parse_string(json_string) # Returns null if parsing failed.
---CHUNK---
